& news
==============================================================================
                        deMUSE News and Announcements
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Welcome to deMUSE 2025!

This is a modernized version of the classic TinyMUSE server, descended from
TinyMUSE '97 and TinyMUSE 1.8a4, originally created for deMUSEcracy.

RECENT UPDATES (2025):

* Complete modernization of C codebase
  - ANSI C compliance throughout
  - Memory safety improvements (SAFE_MALLOC/SMART_FREE)
  - Buffer overflow protection (snprintf, strncpy)
  - Extensive security hardening

* Hash-based command dispatch system
  - Fast O(1) command lookup
  - Eliminated gperf dependency
  - Unified hash table system

* Enhanced help system
  - Comprehensive command documentation
  - Organized function reference
  - Programming examples and tutorials

* Parser system framework
  - Support for multiple command parsers
  - Universe system (experimental)
  - Extensible command registration

* Database improvements
  - GoodObject/ValidObject safety checks
  - Parent/child hierarchy system
  - Enhanced attribute system
  - Zone organization

* Communication enhancements
  - Channel system (+channel, +com)
  - Improved mail and board systems
  - Paste/code sharing system
  - Better color code handling

KEY FEATURES:

Building System:
  - Create rooms with @dig
  - Link exits with @open and @link
  - Build objects with @create
  - Parent/child inheritance with @addparent

Programming:
  - 122 built-in functions
  - Powerful attribute-based scripting
  - Trigger system for automation
  - Control flow commands (@switch, @foreach, @cycle)

Communication:
  - Multi-channel system
  - Private paging and whispers
  - Mail and bulletin boards
  - Zone-wide broadcasts

Administration:
  - Database management tools (@dump, @dbck)
  - Player management commands
  - Quota system
  - Power-based permissions

For more information, type 'help' to access the help system.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------

& version
deMUSE Server Version Information

Version: 2025.01 (Modernized)
Based on: TinyMUSE '97 / TinyMUSE 1.8a4
Original: TinyMUD by Larry Foard
Heritage: TinyMUD → TinyMUSH → TinyMUSE → deMUSE

Modernization Date: January 2025
Platform: Linux (POSIX-compliant)
Language: ANSI C11

Major Components:
  - Command Parser (hash-based dispatch)
  - Expression Evaluator (122 functions)
  - Database System (flat-file, backward compatible)
  - Network I/O (descriptor-based)
  - Attribute System (extensible properties)
  - Zone/Universe Organization

For detailed changelogs, see the source repository.

& welcome
Welcome to deMUSE!

This is a text-based multi-user simulation environment where you can:

  * Explore virtual worlds
  * Interact with other players
  * Build your own spaces and objects
  * Program automated behaviors
  * Participate in collaborative storytelling

To get started:
  - Type 'look' to see your surroundings
  - Type 'help' for the help system
  - Type 'who' to see who else is online
  - Type 'help commands' for a command list

If you're new to MUSEs:
  - MUSEs are text-based worlds
  - Everything is described in text
  - You interact by typing commands
  - You can build and program if you have permission

Type 'news' to see recent updates and announcements.
Type 'help register' if you need to create a character.

Enjoy your time in deMUSE!

& updates
For current updates and changes, type 'news'.

For version information, type 'help version'.

For a complete list of changes, see the source repository changelog.

